{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "16", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "11", "M": "24", "S": "51"}}, "news": [{"title": "Delhi development body's revenue jumps 120% in Q1 FY27", "para": "Delhi Development Authority housing sales reached Rs 1,020 crores in the first quarter. This revenue marks a significant increase from the previous financial year's sales. Narela emerged as the top contributor, selling 1,153 flats during this period. Infrastructure development and improved connectivity are supporting this housing growth. Ongoing schemes are available online on a first-come, first-served basis.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ddas-revenue-surges-120-boosted-by-strong-housing-sales-in-q1-fy27/132437042?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-323149/132437042.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Imperial Holding Group\u2019s long-term vision for luxury real estate in India", "para": "India's luxury real estate market sees a shift towards wellness and lifestyle. Affluent buyers now prioritize privacy and quality of life in their homes. Imperial Holding Group is developing premium mountain communities like Auramah Valley. These developments focus on wellness, nature, and community for residents. The company aims to build destinations offering sustainable value and long-term appreciation.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/brand-connect-initiative/imperial-holding-group-revolutionizing-luxury-real-estate-in-indias-second-home-market/132436939?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-5826461/132436939.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "brand-connect-initiative"}, {"title": "Real estate capital inflows rise 32% to $8.5 billion in H1 2026: Report", "para": "India\u2019s real estate sector recorded equity